> **Why this document exists.** The review requires a named inventory of every
> tool and resource the MCP server exposes — including the administrative
> ones. Omitting a tool the reviewer then discovers via `tools/list` reads as
> concealment. The inventory is tiered by privilege so the access-control
> story is legible, and it reconciles three independently sourced counts so a
> partial view can never masquerade as the whole surface.

